This project includes configuration files that AI tools automatically read. Simply open the project in your IDE, and the AI tool will automatically apply these rules without any manual setup.

### Auto-Discovery Files

- **`.cursor/index.mdc`** - Cursor IDE root rules file (auto-generated, contains core standards + references to detailed rules)
- **`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`** - Cursor IDE individual rule files (auto-generated, one per rule in docs/rules/)
- **`.github/copilot-instructions.md`** - GitHub Copilot automatically reads this file (auto-generated)
- **`replit.md`** - Replit AI automatically reads this file (auto-generated)
- **`AI_INSTRUCTIONS.md`** - Universal master file and single source of truth for all AI tools (edit this to update rules)
- **`.vscode/settings.json`** - VS Code configuration for AI features

### How It Works

1. **Cursor**: Automatically loads rules from `.cursor/index.mdc` (root rules) and `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files (detailed rules, auto-generated). The `index.mdc` contains core standards and references to specific rule files. Just start coding or asking questions - rules are already applied.
   - **`.cursor/index.mdc`**: Root rules file with core standards (same as Copilot/Replit) + references to detailed rule files
   - **`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`**: Individual rule files for specific topics (component-standards, folder-structure, testing, etc.)
   - All files are auto-generated by the `sync-rules` script

2. **GitHub Copilot**: Automatically reads `.github/copilot-instructions.md`. All code suggestions will follow the rules.

3. **VS Code with AI Extensions**: Can reference `AI_INSTRUCTIONS.md` or `.cursorrules` for context. The `.vscode/settings.json` file is configured to recognize markdown rule files.

4. **Claude Code / Other AI Tools**: Can read `.cursorrules` or `AI_INSTRUCTIONS.md` when you reference them or they're in the project context.

