## How to Use Rules with AI Tools

### Method 1: Include Rule File in Prompt

Copy the entire rule document or relevant sections into your AI prompt:

```
Please create a Dashboard component following the rules in component-standards.md.

[Paste component-standards.md content here]

Specifically ensure:
- Performance optimization with React.memo
- Mobile-first responsive design
- CSP and ADA compliance
```

### Method 2: Reference Rule Files

Reference specific rule files in your prompt:

```
I need to create a new component. Please follow these rules:
- docs/rules/component-standards.md
- docs/rules/folder-structure.md

Create a UserProfile component that:
1. Follows the component standards (performance, responsiveness, accessibility)
2. Is placed in the correct folder structure
3. Includes proper TypeScript types
```

### Method 3: Use Rule Checklists

Copy the checklist from rule documents:

```
Create a Button component. Use this checklist:

Component Standards Checklist:
- [ ] Components are memoized when appropriate
- [ ] Expensive calculations use useMemo
- [ ] Function props use useCallback
- [ ] Component tested on mobile (320px+)
- [ ] Component tested on tablet (768px+)
- [ ] Component tested on desktop (1024px+)
- [ ] No inline styles used
- [ ] Semantic HTML elements used
- [ ] ARIA attributes added where needed
- [ ] All interactive elements keyboard accessible
```

